### NestGo sample-app API Playground
# This file is built to work with the VS Code REST Client extension.
# Ensure that your NestGo sample-app is running locally using: nestgo dev

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api

### 1. Welcome / Ping
GET {{baseUrl}}

---

### 2. Register a new user
# @name register
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Jane Developer",
    "email": "jane.developer@example.com",
    "password": "secure123"
}

---

### 3. Login and Generate JWT
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "jane.developer@example.com",
    "password": "secure123"
}

### Ensure that you capture the token from the previous request automatically here if using VS Code.
@token = {{login.response.body.data.token}}

---

### 4. Fetch the authenticated user's profile
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

---

### 5. Fetch all users from PostgreSQL
GET {{baseUrl}}/users

---

### 6. Fetch the user manually using their ID
# Copy the ID created from the login to the request below manually if not using script magic
@userId = {{login.response.body.data.user.id}}

GET {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}}

---

### 7. Update User details
PUT {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Jane Senior Developer"
}

---

### 8. Delete user
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}}
